Boil a half-full #kettle{}.

Halve the @bell pepper{1} and discard the core and seeds. Slice into thin strips.
Cut the @Tenderstem® broccoli{80%g} into thirds.

Zest and cut the @lime{1} into wedges.

Pour the boiled water into a large #saucepan{} with @salt{1/4%tsp} and bring back
to the boil on high heat.

When your pan of water is boiling, add the @egg noodle nest{125%g} and cook until
tender, ~{4%minutes}.

Once cooked, drain in a #sieve{} and run under cold water to stop them sticking
together.

While the noodles cook, heat a drizzle of @oil{1%drizzle} in a large #frying pan{}
on high heat. Drain the @king prawns{150%g}.

Once hot, add the prawns, @sliced mushrooms{120%g}, pepper and broccoli. Season
with @salt{} and @pepper{}. Stir-fry until starting to soften, ~{6-8%minutes}.

> IMPORTANT: Wash hands and utensils after handling raw prawns. Cook so they're
> opaque in the middle.

Stir in the @Thai style spice mix{1%sachet} and @ginger, garlic & lemongrass puree
{15%g} and cook for ~{1%minute} more.

Add the @soy sauce{25%ml}, @ketjap manis{50%g}, @honey{15%g} and
@water{50%ml}(for the sauce) to the pan.

> TIP: If your honey has hardened, pop it in a bowl of hot water for 1 min.

Stir to combine and simmer until slightly thickened, ~{2-3%minutes}.

Add the cooked noodles and a good squeeze of lime juice from a lime wedge to the
pan. Toss to coat in the sauce, ~{1%minute}.

When ready, share your prawn stir-fry between your #serving bowls{}.

Sprinkle over the lime zest and serve with any remaining lime wedges for
squeezing over.

Enjoy!